1
00:01:30,390 --> 00:01:34,979
[Deep Lurk]

2
00:01:35,479 --> 00:01:37,850
[Episode 1]

3
00:01:38,039 --> 00:01:39,240
In 1939,

4
00:01:39,509 --> 00:01:40,690
the Kuomintang military advisor

5
00:01:40,690 --> 00:01:42,710
Qu Wenzhi defected to the Japanese army

6
00:01:42,710 --> 00:01:43,530
and secretly plotted to assassinate

7
00:01:43,530 --> 00:01:45,229
Xue Yue, the commander of the Ninth War Zone.

8
00:01:45,229 --> 00:01:47,000
The plot was uncovered by our party's undercover agents

9
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,460
and was promptly stopped.

10
00:01:49,020 --> 00:01:50,850
Qu Wenzhi, carrying the defense map of Changsha,

11
00:01:50,850 --> 00:01:51,850
fled to Shanghai,

12
00:01:51,979 --> 00:01:53,289
intending to hand over important intelligence

13
00:01:53,289 --> 00:01:55,770
to the Japanese spy, Viscount.

14
00:01:58,009 --> 00:01:59,539
With five more seconds,

15
00:01:59,140 --> 00:02:01,060
[Investigation statistics Bureau]

16
00:01:59,750 --> 00:02:01,950
the commander of the Ninth War Zone

17
00:02:01,970 --> 00:02:04,100
would have died in the Japanese assassination plan.

18
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:05,410
And you still have the nerve to say

19
00:02:05,410 --> 00:02:06,680
that your security measures

20
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:08,150
were theoretically flawless?

21
00:02:08,150 --> 00:02:09,550
It was our fault for being negligent.

22
00:02:09,550 --> 00:02:10,310
What's even more ridiculous is that the people

23
00:02:10,310 --> 00:02:13,100
who stopped this assassination plan were actually from the Communist Party.

24
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:14,510
This is simply a disgrace,

25
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:15,670
a huge disgrace.

26
00:02:15,830 --> 00:02:16,430
Director,

27
00:02:16,590 --> 00:02:18,390
we will definitely investigate it thoroughly.

28
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:21,130
[Ke Jingping, Chief of the Kuomintang NBIS Hunan Station]

29
00:02:19,250 --> 00:02:21,380
Send someone to Shanghai immediately

30
00:02:21,510 --> 00:02:22,710
to capture Qu Wenzhi.

31
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:32,660
At Shanghai Railway Station,

32
00:02:32,530 --> 00:02:33,570
[Shanghai Railway Station]

33
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:34,070
the Japanese military police

34
00:02:34,070 --> 00:02:35,950
and the No. 76 Operation Team of the Wang's Puppet Government

35
00:02:35,950 --> 00:02:36,829
are fully armed

36
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,320
to protect Qu Wenzhi.

37
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:39,400
Meanwhile,

38
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:43,300
[A member of the Kuomintang NBIS operation team]

39
00:02:39,430 --> 00:02:40,630
the Kuomintang NBIS sent people

40
00:02:40,630 --> 00:02:41,990
to track down Qu Wenzhi

41
00:02:42,190 --> 00:02:43,950
and intercept the intelligence.

42
00:02:43,950 --> 00:02:46,320
Cheng Huize, the chief of the NBIS Shanghai Station,

43
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:48,280
sent people to assassinate Qu Wenzhi.

44
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:48,990
I want him alive.

45
00:02:48,350 --> 00:02:50,740
[Cheng Huize, Chief of the Kuomintang NBIS Shanghai Station]

46
00:02:50,070 --> 00:02:50,510
Yes.

47
00:02:51,470 --> 00:02:52,400
Within moments,

48
00:02:52,420 --> 00:02:54,730
the people from the three parties waiting at the train station

49
00:02:54,730 --> 00:02:56,110
are at a tense standoff.

50
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:58,310
Sir,

51
00:02:58,340 --> 00:03:00,200
can you take me to Aihua Hospital?

52
00:03:01,770 --> 00:03:04,020
The rickshaw pullers aren't picking up passengers;

53
00:03:04,020 --> 00:03:06,080
the cigarette vendor is distracted.

54
00:03:07,550 --> 00:03:08,950
Cigarettes!

55
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,570
And the cleaner is only sweeping one spot.

56
00:03:15,830 --> 00:03:17,760
There's even a familiar face here.

57
00:03:18,829 --> 00:03:20,030
Yuan Bengang.

58
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,790
[Yuan Bengang, Leader of the No. 76 Operation Team of the Wang's Puppet Government]

59
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:23,210
Look.

60
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:25,610
Even Chief Takahashi from the Military Police Command

61
00:03:24,010 --> 00:03:25,790
[Takahashi, Chief of the Japanese Military Police Command]

62
00:03:25,650 --> 00:03:26,650
is here in person.

63
00:03:29,150 --> 00:03:31,120
[Yun Hongshen, Second Young Master of the Yun family]

64
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:31,250
There's also Viscount, who's so mysterious

65
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:33,070
it's as if he doesn't exist.

66
00:03:33,790 --> 00:03:36,010
[Viscount, Japanese agent]

67
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:38,720
It seems that today, this train station

68
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:40,579
is truly a gathering of big shots.

69
00:03:41,420 --> 00:03:42,340
Second Young Master,

70
00:03:42,340 --> 00:03:43,870
if anything really happens later,

71
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:44,770
please don't...

72
00:03:44,770 --> 00:03:46,040
Don't act rashly.

73
00:03:46,079 --> 00:03:47,710
Don't make decisions on my own.

74
00:03:47,710 --> 00:03:50,510
Follow Mr. Yun's instructions in everything. Right?

75
00:03:50,510 --> 00:03:51,190
Yes, yes.

76
00:03:53,980 --> 00:03:55,630
[Xu Meijia, Japanese agent]

77
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,150
Cigarettes.

78
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:04,030
Isn't that my dear Uncle Cheng's

79
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:06,150
most trusted assistant, Zheng He?

80
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:09,050
The NBIS sent people here too?

81
00:04:09,430 --> 00:04:09,950
Second Young Master,

82
00:04:09,950 --> 00:04:11,150
Yuan is making a move.

83
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:27,640
I understood.

84
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:29,800
What did you understand?

85
00:04:30,790 --> 00:04:33,320
Obviously, Yuan is measuring the wind speed.

86
00:04:35,470 --> 00:04:36,350
There's...

87
00:04:42,130 --> 00:04:43,750
a sniper of theirs on top of this building.

88
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:45,210
[A sniper of the No. 76 Operation Team of the Wang's Puppet Government]

89
00:04:43,870 --> 00:04:45,470
I'd rather he be dead

90
00:04:45,870 --> 00:04:48,070
than fall into the hands of the Chinese.

91
00:04:59,420 --> 00:05:02,950
So there's a third party waiting to seize the fruits of victory.

92
00:05:03,210 --> 00:05:04,870
This person, whom Viscount came

93
00:05:04,870 --> 00:05:07,100
to pick up himself, must be an important figure.

94
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:08,900
The guy from No. 76 and Takahashi

95
00:05:09,220 --> 00:05:11,820
must be here to protect this important figure.

96
00:05:11,950 --> 00:05:12,790
And the NBIS

97
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:15,460
doesn't want Viscount to meet this important person,

98
00:05:14,790 --> 00:05:18,240
[A sniper of the Kuomintang NBIS]

99
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:17,430
so they took action as well.

100
00:05:19,910 --> 00:05:21,750
They might be here to hunt,

101
00:05:22,150 --> 00:05:24,350
but given the situation today,

102
00:05:24,740 --> 00:05:26,550
they're more likely the prey.

103
00:05:27,590 --> 00:05:28,830
With so many Japanese

104
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:30,940
and their lackeys in this square,

105
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:34,050
and so many of their informants upstairs,

106
00:05:34,790 --> 00:05:36,450
whatever the NBIS plans to do,

107
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:38,340
they're bound to be surrounded.

108
00:05:39,610 --> 00:05:40,610
So,

109
00:05:40,950 --> 00:05:42,390
we need to help them.

110
00:05:43,150 --> 00:05:44,300
We can't.

111
00:05:44,390 --> 00:05:46,030
Mr. Yun has repeatedly emphasized

112
00:05:46,030 --> 00:05:47,490
that our team's only mission

113
00:05:47,490 --> 00:05:48,750
is to follow Viscount.

114
00:05:48,780 --> 00:05:50,460
No matter what happens during this time,

115
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:51,659
we cannot intervene.

116
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:54,960
We are all Chinese; how can we just stand by and watch someone die?

117
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:55,760
Besides,

118
00:05:56,550 --> 00:05:59,350
it's too late for us to avoid getting involved now.

119
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:00,620
Why?

120
00:06:00,870 --> 00:06:03,150
How long has our car been parked here?

121
00:06:03,470 --> 00:06:05,260
It's been sitting here with no one getting out.

122
00:06:05,260 --> 00:06:06,990
Doesn't that seem suspicious?

123
00:06:07,010 --> 00:06:07,850
Besides,

124
00:06:08,110 --> 00:06:09,570
are you sure that the eyes upstairs

125
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:10,930
haven't noticed us?

126
00:06:11,410 --> 00:06:12,070
Don't move.

127
00:06:12,380 --> 00:06:14,570
These bastards are always villainous.

128
00:06:14,570 --> 00:06:17,020
They can make something out of nothing.

129
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:17,920
Moreover,

130
00:06:18,310 --> 00:06:20,170
we're actually doing something.

131
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:22,590
But there are only three of us.

132
00:06:22,690 --> 00:06:25,220
Can't three people accomplish great things?

133
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:27,380
The exact time we arrived here

134
00:06:27,410 --> 00:06:28,410
was 9:19.

135
00:06:28,710 --> 00:06:30,230
And anyone who entered the building

136
00:06:30,230 --> 00:06:31,420
after 9:00 with an unfamiliar face

137
00:06:31,420 --> 00:06:33,680
is likely the person you're looking for.

138
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,460
After taking down the sniper,

139
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:37,280
stay there and keep an eye on things.

140
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:39,030
Once chaos breaks out in the square,

141
00:06:39,030 --> 00:06:40,900
kill Yuan

142
00:06:41,210 --> 00:06:42,670
and pull out immediately.

143
00:06:43,970 --> 00:06:45,610
Cigarettes!

144
00:07:36,290 --> 00:07:36,820
Let's go!

145
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:59,310
Viscount is too hard to take down.

146
00:07:59,310 --> 00:08:01,150
If something unexpected happens,

147
00:08:01,150 --> 00:08:02,750
he definitely won't show up.

148
00:08:03,130 --> 00:08:04,750
Go and keep an eye on Xu Meijia.

149
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,270
If she shows any suspicious behavior,

150
00:08:06,270 --> 00:08:07,120
report immediately.

151
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:07,600
Yes.

152
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:35,409
Let's go!

153
00:09:07,350 --> 00:09:10,010
Our sniper should have already been taken down.

154
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:11,560
Implement Plan B.

155
00:09:11,940 --> 00:09:12,580
Yes.

156
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:28,480
Call the people from No. 76

157
00:09:28,810 --> 00:09:30,120
and tell them that a wanted

158
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:30,790
anti-Japanese activist

159
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:32,720
was spotted near the train station

160
00:09:33,190 --> 00:09:34,690
and that the person got into a car

161
00:09:34,690 --> 00:09:36,690
with the license plate number 0231.

162
00:09:37,460 --> 00:09:38,990
Isn't that Viscount's car?

163
00:09:39,140 --> 00:09:39,670
Exactly.

164
00:09:40,630 --> 00:09:42,630
I want to make them fight each other.

165
00:09:43,010 --> 00:09:45,870
Those traitors will certainly latch onto Viscount

166
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:48,660
once they hear there's a chance for credit.

167
00:09:48,660 --> 00:09:49,260
This way,

168
00:09:50,050 --> 00:09:51,910
we'll have an opportunity to act.

169
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,100
Why do you want to hold back Viscount?

170
00:09:57,100 --> 00:09:59,370
That important figure is not dead.

171
00:09:59,990 --> 00:10:01,020
That's impossible.

172
00:10:01,020 --> 00:10:03,280
I saw him being shot dead with my own eyes.

173
00:10:08,850 --> 00:10:10,710
That must have been a body double.

174
00:10:11,130 --> 00:10:11,930
A body double?

175
00:10:12,090 --> 00:10:13,750
He was shot dead by Takahashi.

176
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:17,450
When he ran over there with the Japanese military police,

177
00:10:17,730 --> 00:10:19,660
he didn't even look at that person,

178
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:22,060
only focusing on finding the people from the NBIS.

179
00:10:22,060 --> 00:10:23,260
What does this prove?

180
00:10:23,370 --> 00:10:25,830
The person who died wasn't important at all;

181
00:10:25,890 --> 00:10:28,090
the real target had already been moved.

182
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:37,580
[Qu Wenzhi, the military advisor who defected from the Ninth War Zone]

183
00:10:36,890 --> 00:10:37,980
Sorry, Mr. Qu,

184
00:10:38,290 --> 00:10:39,550
for making you suffer.

185
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:41,610
Miss Xu,

186
00:10:42,430 --> 00:10:43,630
they won't let me off.

187
00:10:44,140 --> 00:10:45,310
They didn't succeed this time, so there will be a next time.

188
00:10:45,310 --> 00:10:46,480
If they fail next time, there will be another after that.

189
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,210
In short, they will never let me off.

190
00:10:48,210 --> 00:10:49,340
I've been completely sincere.

191
00:10:49,340 --> 00:10:51,300
You must ensure my safety.

192
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:52,750
Second Young Master,

193
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:55,010
I think your analysis makes perfect sense.

194
00:10:55,010 --> 00:10:56,570
After the chaos broke out in the square,

195
00:10:56,570 --> 00:10:58,330
Xu Meijia got out of the car alone

196
00:10:58,330 --> 00:11:01,190
and got into a delivery truck of Tous Red Wine House.

197
00:11:18,660 --> 00:11:20,350
[Tous Red Wine House]

198
00:11:21,170 --> 00:11:22,100
That matches up.

199
00:11:22,940 --> 00:11:23,910
They got that person

200
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:26,860
into the wine house's delivery truck and took him away.

201
00:11:26,860 --> 00:11:29,060
That's why I need to hold back Viscount.

202
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:32,410
We absolutely can't let him see that person.

203
00:11:32,870 --> 00:11:34,790
It's unrelated to our mission.

204
00:11:35,150 --> 00:11:37,450
We've already broken enough rules today.

205
00:11:37,450 --> 00:11:38,730
If Mr. Yun finds out,

206
00:11:39,210 --> 00:11:41,020
we'll all be doomed.

207
00:11:42,260 --> 00:11:45,350
When you're on a mission, sometimes you can't just follow orders.

208
00:11:45,350 --> 00:11:47,090
This is an emergency situation,

209
00:11:47,090 --> 00:11:48,890
so we need to handle it flexibly.

210
00:11:50,470 --> 00:11:51,550
Hurry up.

211
00:11:52,450 --> 00:11:53,920
I have follow-up plans to carry out.

212
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:55,320
Don't mess up my big move.

213
00:11:56,850 --> 00:11:57,330
Go.

214
00:11:57,790 --> 00:11:58,550
Go.

215
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:03,650
Second Young Master,

216
00:12:03,650 --> 00:12:05,050
you really can't do this.

217
00:12:05,230 --> 00:12:06,600
Mr. Yun has repeatedly emphasized

218
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,050
that this Viscount is not easy to deal with.

219
00:12:08,050 --> 00:12:09,510
He's extremely cautious.

220
00:12:09,670 --> 00:12:11,240
Even if you manage to hold him back,

221
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,830
it won't be easy to wrap things up.

222
00:12:12,830 --> 00:12:14,380
If this traces back to you,

223
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:16,850
won't both you and Mr. Yun both be exposed?

224
00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:20,380
Why did I have Zhou use that gun earlier?

225
00:12:22,630 --> 00:12:23,750
Kill Yuan.

226
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:28,280
That's a standard-issue weapon for NBIS agents.

227
00:12:29,890 --> 00:12:31,350
You're not thinking of...

228
00:12:31,780 --> 00:12:33,150
The Japanese sniper

229
00:12:33,170 --> 00:12:35,220
was taken down by the people from the NBIS.

230
00:12:35,220 --> 00:12:37,180
The person who called No. 76

231
00:12:37,380 --> 00:12:38,730
to report Viscount was

232
00:12:39,140 --> 00:12:40,800
also from the NBIS, of course.

233
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:42,280
Thank you, sir.

234
00:12:43,110 --> 00:12:46,370
When I get the bounty, I'll be sure to show you my gratitude.

235
00:12:46,490 --> 00:12:47,150
Okay, okay.

236
00:12:47,350 --> 00:12:47,990
Goodbye.

237
00:12:53,470 --> 00:12:54,610
Second Young Master,

238
00:12:54,610 --> 00:12:57,160
why are you so determined to do this?

239
00:12:57,450 --> 00:12:58,650
Out of curiosity.

240
00:13:00,350 --> 00:13:00,950
Mr. Yun,

241
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:02,440
there's an emergency.

242
00:13:03,270 --> 00:13:05,720
The person important enough to prompt Viscount to take action

243
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,670
would be immensely useful to us

244
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:10,180
if we can keep him under our control.

245
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:13,530
Actually,

246
00:13:13,550 --> 00:13:15,950
I do have a bit of a personal motive for this.

247
00:13:16,220 --> 00:13:17,300
I want to use him

248
00:13:17,570 --> 00:13:19,700
to trade for something with my father.

249
00:14:03,210 --> 00:14:04,010
Cigarettes.

250
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:05,670
Sir, take a look.

251
00:14:07,190 --> 00:14:08,120
Cigarettes!

252
00:14:16,790 --> 00:14:17,260
[Tous Red Wine House]

253
00:14:26,370 --> 00:14:27,230
I'm sorry, Sir.

254
00:14:27,710 --> 00:14:29,730
All the VIP wine-tasting rooms upstairs are occupied.

255
00:14:29,730 --> 00:14:30,290
Perhaps

256
00:14:30,490 --> 00:14:31,690
you could make do by taking a seat

257
00:14:31,690 --> 00:14:33,420
at one of the booths for a while?

258
00:14:33,490 --> 00:14:34,570
I'm terribly sorry.

259
00:14:34,570 --> 00:14:35,100
Alright.

260
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:37,160
This way, please.

261
00:14:38,910 --> 00:14:39,510
Thank you.

262
00:14:52,140 --> 00:14:53,070
Excuse me, Miss.

263
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:55,000
May I ask who you are looking for?

264
00:14:56,260 --> 00:14:58,320
[Wen Yeming, an agent from the Kuomintang NBIS Hunan Station]

265
00:14:57,670 --> 00:14:58,560
Just now,

266
00:14:58,650 --> 00:15:00,670
a gentleman called our restaurant

267
00:15:00,690 --> 00:15:01,540
to order sushi

268
00:15:01,740 --> 00:15:03,530
and requested it be delivered here.

269
00:15:03,530 --> 00:15:05,130
He said he would be in Private Room No. 1.

270
00:15:05,130 --> 00:15:06,720
I kindly ask that you make an exception.

271
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,940
I must deliver the sushi to the guest personally.

272
00:15:08,940 --> 00:15:09,540
Please.

273
00:15:09,770 --> 00:15:10,780
Please wait a moment.

274
00:15:10,780 --> 00:15:12,510
I need to confirm with my guest.

275
00:15:12,770 --> 00:15:14,080
Thank you.

276
00:15:14,510 --> 00:15:15,440
You're welcome.

277
00:15:24,810 --> 00:15:26,140
Would you like to order anything else?

278
00:15:26,140 --> 00:15:28,140
Hello, what would you like to drink?

